title: Justin Trudeau, The Leader of Canada’s Liberal Party, has unseated the Conservative prime minister, Stephen Harper,
text:
Share Justin trudeau 
Justin Trudeau is poised to be Canada’s next prime minister, leading the Liberal Party to a win and ending nine years of Conservative rule, CBC News is projecting. 
It is still unclear whether Trudeau’s Liberals will form a minority or majority government. CBC News made the projection as polls have closed in almost all of the provinces and the bulk of the results of the federal election are pouring in. 
Eyes will now turn to the results in Quebec and Ontario to see what inroads the Liberals have made in the two provinces.
